snippet.textDisplay: I have been pierced by hair. In my FOOT. It looked like at first it was just a hair with the pointy end glued to my foot but then I tried to pull it away and it just stayed in. I took some tweezers and the hair broke off. Now I could see just how deep into my skin it was. I only noticed it because when I was taking steps in my shower on that one specific spot in my foot I would feel this painful pressure under my skin and now I knew why. So I basicially tried to dig into my foot with nail clippers, scissors and the tweezers again and ended up messing my foot up that badly that I couldn't walk on it at all for 3 days without bandages...So I went from slight pain and pressure in my foot to an open wound I did to myself. And the best part is the hair is still in there. It doesnt hurt anymore though so I guess that's good

snippet.textDisplay: Can confirm that I'm a statistical "at least one" person and did have colorful hair.  After two decades of average haircuts and nothing else being done to my hair, I went all in and dyed all of it (and consequently my shower and several shirts) blue.  I lucked out when it faded, though, in that all the lighter blues and blue-greens it went through matched my eyes, so I still liked it when I stopped re-dyeing it.
